30-Second Interview Answer

DBMS is better than a file system because it reduces data redundancy and inconsistency, provides better security, 
supports concurrent access, ensures data integrity, offers backup and recovery mechanisms, and allows easy data retrieval through SQL queries.
These features make data management more efficient, reliable, and secure than traditional file systems. 🎯

